## Convert PDFs (and other binary docs) for ontology generation via `ai_parse_document`

Context: Uploaded documents could be PDFs/Office/images (the upload input has no
type filter and the UI previews them), but the OWL-generator and business-rules
agents read documents through `tool_read_document`, which did a raw UTF-8 decode
and returned `"Binary file – cannot read as text"` for any binary file. As a
result, PDFs uploaded by users never actually fed ontology generation. This
change converts binary documents to markdown on the fly, at read time, using the
Databricks `ai_parse_document` SQL function on the configured SQL warehouse, with
a graceful fallback to the previous behaviour when no warehouse is available.

Changes:

1. src/agents/tools/context.py
   Added `warehouse_id: str = ""` to `ToolContext` so document tools can reach a
   SQL warehouse for binary parsing. Empty means "no warehouse" (binary docs are
   skipped, no regression for text docs).
2. src/agents/tools/documents.py
   - Added `_PARSEABLE_BINARY_EXT` (pdf/png/jpg/jpeg/docx/doc/pptx/ppt) and
     `_file_extension` helper.
   - Added `_parse_binary_document(ctx, file_path)`: builds a `DatabricksClient`
     from `(host, token, warehouse_id)` and runs
     `SELECT to_json(ai_parse_document(content, map('version', '2.0'))) FROM READ_FILES(<path>, format => 'binaryFile')`
     (output schema pinned to v2.0),
     then extracts markdown via `_extract_markdown_from_parsed`. Verified live
     against the workspace: `ai_parse_document` returns output schema v2.0 where
     text lives in `document.elements[].content` (figures expose an AI
     `description`) and `document.pages[]` carries only `id`/`image_uri`. The
     extractor prefers elements, then falls back to page `content`, then a
     top-level markdown blob. Returns `None` (caller falls back) when no
     warehouse is set or the
     query/parse fails or yields nothing. Caches parsed text per file path on the
     context to avoid re-parsing within a single agent run.
   - Refactored truncation/payload into `_doc_payload(...)` and branched
     `tool_read_document`: parseable binary extensions go through the parser
     (returning `parsed_with: "ai_parse_document"`), unknown-extension binaries
     fall back to the parser on UTF-8 decode failure, and plain text keeps the
     existing decode path. Updated the `read_document` tool description.
3. src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py
   `run_agent` accepts `warehouse_id` and sets it on the `ToolContext`.
4. src/agents/agent_business_rules_generator/engine.py
   `run_agent` accepts `warehouse_id` and sets it on the `ToolContext` (shares the
   same document tool).
5. src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py
   `generate_with_agent` and `generate_rules_with_agent` accept `warehouse_id`
   and forward it to the respective agent `run_agent`.
6. src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py
   Imported `resolve_warehouse_id`; `/ontology/wizard/generate-async` and
   `/ontology/business-rules/generate-async` resolve the warehouse and pass it
   into the agent calls.
7. tests/units/agents/test_documents_tool.py (new)
   Covers `_extract_markdown_from_parsed` (pages/elements/markdown/empty), text
   files unchanged, binary-without-warehouse error, binary-with-warehouse parse
   (mocked `DatabricksClient.execute_query`), per-run caching, truncation, and
   warehouse-failure fallback.
8. docs/data-access.md
   Documented binary-document conversion via `ai_parse_document`, the warehouse
   requirement, and the supported formats.

Modified files:
- src/agents/tools/context.py
- src/agents/tools/documents.py
- src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py
- src/agents/agent_business_rules_generator/engine.py
- src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py
- src/api/routers/internal/ontology.py
- tests/units/agents/test_documents_tool.py (new)
- docs/data-access.md

Verification: confirmed `ai_parse_document` end-to-end on the live workspace
