## "New Assistant" — guided Business View creation from selected entities + neighbours

Context: Business Views (the Visual Ontology Designer) only offered a blank
"Create View" that hides every entity, leaving the curator to reveal nodes one
by one from the palette. This adds a "New Assistant" button that bootstraps a
view from a chosen set of seed entities plus their ontology neighbours, with a
1–3 hop depth control. Frontend-only: no backend changes were needed since
`/domain/design-views/*` already persists per-view `visibility` and OntoViz
`fromJSON` honours `hiddenEntities` / `hiddenRelationships` / `hiddenInheritances`.

Changes:

1. src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_design.html
   Added the `#newAssistantBtn` ("New Assistant", magic icon) to the Business
   Views toolbar, between the view CRUD group and the "Create Group" button.
2. src/front/static/global/js/ontology-design.js
   - Extracted `_buildFreshDesignLayout(visibleNames=null)` from
     `loadFromOntologyFresh` (DRY): builds entities/relationships/inheritances
     from `OntologyState` and computes visibility. `null` hides everything
     (legacy fresh-view behaviour, `hiddenInheritances` kept empty); a Set keeps
     only that subset visible and hides the rest (entities, relationships, and
     inheritances). `loadFromOntologyFresh` now delegates to it.
   - Added `_computeOntologyNeighborhood(seedNames, depth)`: builds an
     undirected adjacency from object properties (domain↔range) and inheritance
     (child↔parent), resolves URI-or-name domain/range values, and BFS-expands
     the seeds by `depth` hops (1–3).
   - Added `showNewAssistantDialog()`: Bootstrap modal with a name field, a
     searchable/select-all checkbox list of all entities, and a 1/2/3-hop depth
     selector. On confirm it creates the view (`/domain/design-views/create`),
     refreshes the list, switches to it (`/domain/design-views/switch`), renders
     the curated subset via `_buildFreshDesignLayout(visible)` and persists it
     (`/domain/design-views/save-current`).
   - Wired `#newAssistantBtn` in `initViewManagement`; disabled it for
     read-only versions in `refreshViewList`.
