## Collapse / expand entities in Business Views

Context: Dense Business Views can be hard to read when every entity shows its
full property list. This adds the ability to collapse an entity to a compact
header-only card (and expand it back), both per-entity and for the whole view.
Collapse state is persisted per view via `visibility.collapsedEntities`, which
already round-trips through `/domain/design-views/save-current` and the OntoViz
`toJSON`/`fromJSON` visibility plumbing — so no backend change was required.

Changes:

1. src/front/static/global/ontoviz/ontoviz.js
   - `Entity`: added a `collapsed` field (constructor + `toJSON`).
   - `_renderEntity`: added an always-visible chevron toggle (`▾`/`▸`,
     `data-action="toggle-collapse"`) in the entity header; when collapsed the
     card adds `.ovz-collapsed` and skips the description/body/inherited/
     add-property sections while keeping the connectors so relationships still
     attach.
   - `_bindEntityEvents`: toggle handler flips `collapsed`, re-renders, updates
     relationship paths, and fires `onEntityUpdate` (auto-save).
   - `getVisibilityState`/`setVisibilityState`: persist & restore
     `collapsedEntities` (by name); collapse is applied before the hidden pass
     so hidden re-rendered nodes stay hidden.
   - `fromJSON`: collapse flagged entities before first render (no flicker).
   - New public API: `setAllCollapsed(bool)`, `collapseAll()`, `expandAll()`,
     `hasCollapsedEntities()`.
2. src/front/static/global/ontoviz/css/ontoviz-entity.css
   Styles for `.ovz-entity-collapse-btn` and the `.ovz-collapsed` header-only
   card (no bottom border, full radius).
3. src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_ontology_design.html
   Added the `#toggleCollapseAllBtn` ("Collapse all / Expand all") toolbar
