## Fix: empty Business-View state — dropdown, ontology wipe on delete, Create Group

Context: After enabling deletion of the last Business View, three problems
surfaced in the no-views state:
(1) the view dropdown showed a stray "null"/placeholder entry;
(2) deleting the last view wiped the ontology — clearing the canvas fires
OntoViz `onEntityDelete`/`onRelationshipDelete` callbacks, each scheduling an
auto-save, and the debounced `syncDesignToOntology` then wrote the now-empty
canvas back over `OntologyState.config.classes` (so "New Assistant" reported
"No entities available in the ontology yet");
(3) "Create Group" stayed enabled with no view open.

Changes:

1. src/front/static/global/js/ontology-design.js
   - `refreshViewList`: when there are no views, the dropdown is now emptied
     (`innerHTML = ''`) and disabled instead of showing a placeholder option.
   - `refreshViewList`: `#createGroupFromViewBtn` is disabled when no view is
     open (operates on the current view's entities).
   - Delete confirm handler (no-views branch): cancel any pending auto-save,
     reset `layoutDirty`, and set `isLoadingData = true` around
     `ontologyDesigner.clear()` so the delete callbacks can't trigger a sync
     that overwrites the ontology. This is the root-cause fix for the wipe.

