## Fix: collapse/expand-all resurrected hidden entities and relationships

Context: After hiding an entity or relationship (via the visibility palette or
the new right-click "Hide from view"), clicking the global collapse/expand-all
toolbar button made the hidden elements reappear. Root cause: `setAllCollapsed`
calls `_renderEntity` / `_updateRelationshipPaths`, which rebuild the DOM
elements from scratch. Hiding only sets `style.display = 'none'` on the existing
element (visibility lives in `visibilityState`, not in the rebuilt markup), so
the freshly rendered elements came back visible.

Changes:

1. src/front/static/global/ontoviz/ontoviz.js
   - `_renderEntity()`: after appending the rebuilt element, reapply
     `display:none` when `visibilityState.entities.get(id) === false`, so any
     re-render path preserves the hidden state.
   - `setAllCollapsed()`: after `_updateRelationshipPaths()` (which re-renders
     connections), call `_updateAllConnectionsVisibility()` to reapply hidden
     relationship/inheritance state.

