## Domain status lifecycle (DRAFT / IN-REVIEW / PUBLISHED)

Context: Domain versions previously used a single "Active" (`mcp_enabled`)
toggle to pick which version the API/MCP served, with editability gated only by
"is this the latest version". This introduces a proper lifecycle status per
version — `DRAFT` → `IN-REVIEW` → `PUBLISHED` — that gates editability, gates
API/MCP data access (only PUBLISHED is served, numeric-latest wins), and is
surfaced as a colour-coded badge everywhere a domain+version is shown. The
"Active" toggle is retired; the `mcp_enabled` column is left dormant for a later
migration.

State machine (enforced server-side):
- DRAFT → IN-REVIEW: admin or builder; precondition: version has been built
  (`last_build` set). Locks editing.
- IN-REVIEW → DRAFT: admin or builder. Re-enables editing.
- IN-REVIEW → PUBLISHED: admin or builder.
- PUBLISHED → DRAFT: admin only (reversible publish).
- No direct DRAFT → PUBLISHED. New versions are always created as DRAFT.

