## Lakebase 0.4 → 0.5 upgrade SQL script

Context: The lifecycle feature adds `domain_versions.status` + a CHECK
constraint + an index. The app self-heals the column and index lazily on first
read, but it does not add the CHECK constraint and does not backfill PUBLISHED
from the retired `mcp_enabled` flag. Provided a one-shot, idempotent psql script
so operators can fully migrate an existing 0.4.x Lakebase registry (and keep the
previously "active" version exposed on the API/MCP).

Changes:
1. scripts/upgrade_lakebase_0.4_To_0.5.sql (new) — idempotent migration:
   adds `status` column, the `domain_versions_status_check` constraint (guarded
   via `pg_constraint`), the `idx_domain_versions_status` index; backfills
   `mcp_enabled=true → status='PUBLISHED'`; mirrors status into the `info`
   JSONB blob; prints a status distribution summary. Schema is configurable via
   `-v reg_schema=...` (defaults to `ontobricks_registry`). `mcp_enabled` left
   dormant (no drop).

Modified files:
- scripts/upgrade_lakebase_0.4_To_0.5.sql (new)

