## Fix: PUBLISHED domains had their Knowledge Graph query UI disabled

Context: Reported on the "Contact Center" domain — a PUBLISHED version showed
every Knowledge Graph filter/search control greyed out, so graph exploration
was impossible. Root cause: PUBLISHED/IN-REVIEW now adds `read-only-version` to
`<body>`, and the generic form-field gate in permissions.css disables all
`input`/`select`/`textarea`. Its "keep search/filter/query interactive"
exemptions are (a) case-sensitive id substring matches that miss mixed-case ids
like `sgFilterValue` / `sgSearchValue`, and (b) don't cover `<select>` or
checkbox controls — which is exactly what the Sigma graph Filter/View tabs use.
The Digital Twin page is a read/analysis surface that never edits the domain
design, so the whole page should stay interactive; real mutations are still
enforced server-side by `PermissionMiddleware`.

Changes:
1. src/front/templates/base.html — added `data-page="{% block page_id %}{%
   endblock %}"` to `<body>` so pages can self-identify.
2. src/front/templates/dtwin.html — sets `{% block page_id %}digitaltwin{%
   endblock %}`.
3. src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css — the generic read-only
   form-field gate now excludes `body[data-page="digitaltwin"]`, so the Digital
   Twin's filter/search/query/reasoning/cohort controls stay usable on
   PUBLISHED/IN-REVIEW versions and for viewers. The Build/sync status gate
   (`body.read-only-status #syncStartBtn`) is unaffected and still blocks builds
   on non-DRAFT versions.
4. Status-badge readability: the static `.js-version-status-badge` placeholders
   in the dtwin/ontology/domain templates used the pale `text-warning` initial
   class; switched to `text-dark` to match the runtime badges.

